{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":89638,"duration_api_ms":87633,"num_turns":4,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"1d51e3a7-323d-49bc-9d4b-6f50b5a9f50f","total_cost_usd":0.31943740000000004,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":24015,"cache_read_input_tokens":111335,"output_tokens":1632,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":24015,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":5,"outputTokens":1632,"cacheReadInputTokens":111335,"cacheCreationInputTokens":24015,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.24658625,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":71,"outputTokens":4956,"cacheReadInputTokens":271914,"cacheCreationInputTokens":16647,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.07285115,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Independently verified all three amendments against the actual code in fs.rs and model.rs. Amendment fr-9-ed4ab282 identifies a genuine defensive gap in the function signature contract. Amendment fr-9-b6508003 correctly flags a fragile implicit coupling between json_fill_none semantics and serde attributes. Amendment fr-9-05edcb4b's concern about non-canonical outcome representations is unfounded given TaskRunOutcome's deterministic Display impl and snake_case serde rename.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-9-ed4ab282","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified in the code: the two call sites pass (Some, Some) at line 3066-3070 and (None, None) at line 3194-3198, so the (Some(run_id), None) combination never occurs today. However, the function signature freely permits it, and if it occurred, the started_at guard at lines 2823-2828 would be entirely skipped for runless candidates, allowing backfill of the wrong legacy terminal row. A debug_assert!(requested_run_id.is_none() || requested_started_at.is_some()) is trivial to add and would catch any future misuse at the call site immediately. This is a legitimate invariant enforcement issue with a low-cost fix."},{"amendment_id":"fr-9-b6508003","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified that json_fill_none uses entry(key).or_insert(value) which only fills absent keys. All Option fields on StartJournalDetails and CompletionJournalDetails currently use #[serde(default, skip_serializing_if = \"Option::is_none\")], so None fields are omitted from serialization and correctly filled by the overlay. But this coupling is implicit and fragile — a new Option field added without skip_serializing_if would serialize as null, making the key present, and or_insert would skip it. A test verifying the fill behavior plus a doc-comment on the structs requiring the serde attributes is a proportionate defensive measure that costs almost nothing and prevents a subtle future regression."},{"amendment_id":"fr-9-05edcb4b","decision":"reject","rationale":"The concern about non-canonical outcome representations is unfounded. Verified in model.rs that TaskRunOutcome has a hand-written Display impl producing deterministic lowercase strings ('pending', 'running', 'succeeded', 'failed', 'skipped') and uses #[serde(rename_all = \"snake_case\")] for serialization. The outcome field in CompletionJournalDetails is a String, but both code paths that populate it go through the same Display or serde pathway, producing identical strings for identical logical values. There is no realistic scenario where the same outcome would yield different string representations, so the equality check at line 2374 cannot fail spuriously. A canonicity test would be harmless but addresses a non-existent risk."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"a12d8e63-3971-4999-9ef7-f367bbba0834"}
